      "source": [
        "### **Dataset Overview**\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset appears to describe customer information for a **telecommunication service** (likely the *Telco Customer Churn dataset*), focusing on three numeric variables:\n",
        "\n",
        "* **tenure** – how many months a customer has stayed with the company,\n",
        "* **MonthlyCharges** – the amount charged per month,\n",
        "* **TotalCharges** – the total amount a customer has paid so far.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### **1. Tenure**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Range:** 1 to 72 months → customers have stayed from just 1 month up to 6 years.\n",
        "* **Mean:** 32.42 months (~2.7 years).\n",
        "* **Median:** 29 months → distribution slightly **right-skewed** (a few long-term customers).\n",
        "* **Interpretation:** The customer base includes both new and long-term users, but the typical customer stays for around 2–3 years.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### **2. Monthly Charges**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Range:** $18.25 – $118.75 → wide variation in monthly plans.\n",
        "* **Mean:** $64.80, **Median:** $70.35 → slightly **left-skewed** (more customers pay higher monthly charges).\n",
        "* **Interpretation:** Most customers pay moderate to high monthly fees, suggesting multiple service tiers or add-ons.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### **3. Total Charges**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Range:** $18.80 – $8684.80.\n",
        "* **Mean:** $2283.30, **Median:** $1397.48 → **right-skewed** (a few long-tenured customers with very high totals).\n",
        "* **Interpretation:** Total payments depend heavily on tenure and monthly charges, as expected newer customers have low totals, while long-term ones accumulate large totals.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### **4. Relationship Insights (from summary)**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Tenure** and **TotalCharges** are likely **positively correlated**, longer tenure leads to higher total charges.\n",
        "* **MonthlyCharges** varies widely but doesn’t depend strongly on tenure (suggesting different plan types).\n",
        "* High **std. deviation** for TotalCharges (2266.77) reflects a diverse customer base in terms of spending and loyalty.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Overall Inference**\n",
        "\n",
        "* The customer population is **diverse**, with varying subscription lengths and charge levels.\n",
        "* There is evidence of **customer segmentation**, low-charge short-term users vs. high-charge long-term users.\n",
        "* Understanding these distributions can help identify **customer lifetime value** and **potential churn risks** among shorter-tenure or lower-spending segments.\n"
      ]
